South Korea Court Says Samsung, Apple Infringed Each Other's Patents
A South Korea court on Friday delivered a split decision in its part of the global legal battle between Apple and Samsung over mobile patents. The WSJ's Evan Ramstad talks about the legal battle in South Korea and the U.S.
SEOULâ€”A South Korea court on Friday delivered a split decision in its piece of the global legal battle between Apple Inc. and Samsung Electronics Co. over mobile computing patents.
A three-judge panel in Seoul Central District Court said Apple infringed two Samsung technology patents, while Samsung violated one of Apple's patents. The court awarded small damages to both companies and said they must halt sales of the infringing products in South Korea.